gtk2surf 

Version 0.01

Copyright (C) 2009 Rémy Oudompheng
Author: Rémy Oudompheng <oudomphe@math.unice.fr>

Overview
--------

gtk2surf is a graphical front-end for using surf, the command-line driven
rendering tool for algebraic surfaces. It is a translation using GTK2
(and the Gtk-- bindings) of the GTK frontend 'gtksurf' written 
by Johannes Beigel. 

See surf's homepage: http://surf.sourceforge.net
and surf documentation for more information about surf 
syntax and usage.

Requirements
------------

- a C++ compiler, usually GCC 4.

- a make tool, usually GNU make.

- GTK+ 2.12 or later. (http://www.gtk.org/)

- the GTKMM C++ bindings for GTK (http://gtkmm.org/)

- the surf kernel.

Basic installation
------------------

Compilation steps are standard as in other autoconf-generated packages: 

    ./configure
    make
    (become root)
    make install

